CMC Networks is hosting its CMC Annual Enterprise Summit, which will take place at the Bryanston Country Club from 08:30 on 24 May 2022. The summit will feature presentations by thought leaders from Juniper, Microsoft, NetMotion by Absolute, CMC Networks, and many more. Click here to register for the CMC Annual Enterprise Summit These experts will provide cutting-edge insights into topics such as next-generation connectivity, SD-WAN, Secure Access, and the cloud – all of which are underpinned by the largest Pan-African AI-driven backbone network: CMC Networks. If your business is considering a move to the cloud, deploying an SD-WAN, or implementing a Secure Access service offering, then this is an event you cannot afford to miss. The event’s impressive list of Keynote Speakers and Panel includes: Vince Resente – Senior Cloud Architect at Microsoft
Warren Hero – CIO at Webber Wentzel
Palesa Gaasenwe – CIO at SafetyCloud
Stuart Wilson – Group IT Manager at Cerba Lancet Africa
Jon Howes – SSR – SASE and AI at Juniper Networks
Daniel Schapiro – Sales Director for Africa at SES
Binesh George – CEO and Co-Founder of Redvine Networks
Wesley van Rayne – Principal Engineer at Redvine Networks
Achi Lewis – AVP of EMEAI at Absolute Software Speakers from CMC Networks: Marisa Trisolino – CEO of CMC Networks
Craig Lowe – CCO of CMC Networks
Nico Walters – Head of Innovation and Information at CMC Networks
Gerrit Venter – Head of Product at CMC Networks Attendees can arrive from 8:30 and will be treated to refreshments until the conference begins at 9:00. The event will span three hours, after which attendees can enjoy an optional lunch and networking opportunity from 12:00 until 14:00. Click here to register for the CMC Annual Enterprise Summit